{
  "ir_hash": "sha256:790911c3833542552d76b900d38346d320a520a9ddaf211c203f2beb4cbe586c",
  "knowledges": [
    {
      "content": "Perovskite/silicon tandem solar cells on silicon heterojunction bottom cells. Perovskite bandgap 1.69 eV. Device stack: IZO/HTL201/perovskite/LiF/EDAI/C60/SnO2/IZO/Ag/MgF2. Device area 1.004 cm2. Certified by European Solar Test Installation (ESTI).",
      "content_hash": "e890255a50b80f858212d9294b06aa192d075c958f133ca9bd338d6f66b53e6a",
      "declaration_index": 0,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::exp_context",
      "label": "exp_context",
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "setting"
    },
    {
      "content": "Self-assembled monolayers (SAMs) serve as hole-selective layers in inverted PSCs. Symmetric SAMs like Me-4PACz and MeO-4PACz have limited coverage on TCO substrates and non-optimal interaction with perovskites, constraining tandem device performance.",
      "content_hash": "91a628c496897fd947311a20f395ab6a03334ce61c01774b97f349aac2b8533a",
      "declaration_index": 1,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::sam_challenge",
      "label": "sam_challenge",
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "setting"
    },
    {
      "content": "Perovskite/silicon tandem solar cells using asymmetric SAM HTL201 achieve a certified PCE of 34.58% (ESTI certification) with Voc of nearly 2.00 V, representing a record efficiency for perovskite/silicon tandem solar cells",
      "content_hash": "5f3f18d34b104795e9a654878463c38453b2bc90e453883cb68366091e5c65f2",
      "declaration_index": 2,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::certified_34_58",
      "label": "certified_34_58",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.92
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "certified_34_58_percent",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The champion tandem device achieves an in-house PCE of 34.60% with Voc of 2.001 V, Jsc of 20.64 mA cm-2, and FF of 83.79%",
      "content_hash": "5891436981694d602e60a7928a90eb218029c0c4e061a7fe804fbc3f8b1a45be",
      "declaration_index": 3,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::champion_34_60",
      "label": "champion_34_60",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.88
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "champion_34_60_percent",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "An asymmetric self-assembled monolayer (HTL201) featuring an anchoring group and spacer flanking a carbazole core shows minimized steric hindrance and improved coverage on IZO recombination layer compared to symmetric SAMs (Me-4PACz, MeO-4PACz)",
      "content_hash": "88ee4284cc1d9e8aef898bd66704b2e426ed8bab169ce44831e23025dcc7e358",
      "declaration_index": 4,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::asymmetric_sam_htl201",
      "label": "asymmetric_sam_htl201",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.85
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "asymmetric_sam_htl201",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "HTL201 forms denser monolayer coverage on IZO substrates than Me-4PACz and MeO-4PACz, with higher coverage factor confirmed by XPS and molecular dynamics simulations showing stronger adsorption energy",
      "content_hash": "53c1370ff5b037f2c4948cd40aadcf8825b53a89dbb9e2c5494f5223c4296049",
      "declaration_index": 5,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::enhanced_coverage",
      "label": "enhanced_coverage",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.82
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "enhanced_sam_coverage",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Strong coordination interaction between HTL201 and perovskite film effectively reduces non-radiative recombination at the buried interface, achieving PLQY of 0.399% (versus 0.346% for Me-4PACz) and QFLS of 1.270 V on textured silicon substrates",
      "content_hash": "87169e6a01b5bfa35386f0a16c1617c3df7536f29de5c4ad735c3c0f859c5d53",
      "declaration_index": 6,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::buried_interface_passivation",
      "label": "buried_interface_passivation",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.82
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "buried_interface_passivation",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The optimized energy-level alignment between perovskite and HTL201 enables Voc approaching 2.00 V for perovskite/silicon tandems, among the highest reported voltages for this architecture",
      "content_hash": "43f1566b1b98bc6c5fc2201859129c3cd10fb3b53eb451a337bfaff2b3a07c83",
      "declaration_index": 7,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::voc_near_2v",
      "label": "voc_near_2v",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.85
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "voc_near_2_volts",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Perovskite films on HTL201 show carrier lifetime of 5,860 ns versus 5,574 ns on Me-4PACz and 1,813 ns on MeO-4PACz, indicating lower trap density at the buried interface",
      "content_hash": "db0b60243631c5dd274262065ee9be5ad6894ee0b94ef8b03ad73e72d858a563",
      "declaration_index": 8,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::carrier_lifetime_5860ns",
      "label": "carrier_lifetime_5860ns",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.82
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "carrier_lifetime_5860_ns",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Devices using HTL201 achieve an average PCE of 34.22% across 20 devices, compared with 32.18% for Me-4PACz and 33.34% for MeO-4PACz",
      "content_hash": "726512d3ebba46dd49819a4c9a92672ac0b5d3d50964bafee673c17525e4d864",
      "declaration_index": 9,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::avg_pce_34_22",
      "label": "avg_pce_34_22",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.85
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "avg_pce_34_22_percent",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The asymmetric molecular design strategy is generally successful: HTL201-like derivatives HTL207 (n=2) and HTL203 (n=4) also deliver higher efficiency than Me-4PACz and MeO-4PACz, with HTL201 being optimal",
      "content_hash": "bc49255a69479fef2463b2e05d87f5c516659ce382287bbc1e1139686109e10b",
      "declaration_index": 10,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::asymmetric_design_general",
      "label": "asymmetric_design_general",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.78
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "asymmetric_design_general",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "HTL201-coated substrates delay perovskite nucleation and crystallization (nucleation at 540 s vs 180 s for Me-4PACz), effectively improving perovskite film quality and (100) plane orientation",
      "content_hash": "7216b047ce9a3c076ae277349ba2e472f512051282579f299332f5e334868606",
      "declaration_index": 11,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::delayed_crystallization",
      "label": "delayed_crystallization",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.78
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "delayed_crystallization",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Encapsulated HTL201-based tandem devices show stable MPP tracking at 25 C under continuous 1-sun illumination, demonstrating promising operational stability",
      "content_hash": "51d40ed0374f14086c01552aa14ecb0689235f46f5de45fbe18c512699f1366d",
      "declaration_index": 12,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::mppt_stability_25c",
      "label": "mppt_stability_25c",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.7
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "mppt_stability_25c",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Encapsulated HTL201-based tandem devices show degraded but still functional MPP tracking at 45 C, indicating thermal sensitivity of perovskite/Si tandems requires further improvement",
      "content_hash": "6b6e1527c64d623c14381b1467359dd2227c4d571eb114a9501b216f4e28666a",
      "declaration_index": 13,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_he2025::mppt_stability_45c",
      "label": "mppt_stability_45c",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.65
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "title": "mppt_stability_45c",
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Perovskite solar cells can achieve commercially competitive power conversion efficiency exceeding 20%",
      "content_hash": "4d29b70c694c4b3f56d48d07e077f616e92d471d2c91d7d4bb5b07e2de7c7659",
      "declaration_index": 1,
      "exported": false,
